// @check
// @error cannot compare string with i32
// Regression guard for the `==`/`!=` union-symmetry rule: making the union
// check order-independent must NOT loosen `==` into accepting genuinely
// incomparable operands. With no value-union in play, a plain type mismatch
// (`"a" == 7` — `string` vs `i32`, neither an arm of any union) is still a
// type error.
if "a" == 7 { print(1) }
